article.headline: Alabama A&M 31, Prairie View 16
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas (AP) -- Kelcy Luke threw two touchdown passes and ran for another score as Alabama A&M overcame a slow start to beat Prairie View A&M 31-16 Saturday night. Alabama A&M (9-2, 7-2 Southwestern) trailed 6-0 at halftime, but Luke threw a 15-yard touchdown pass to Timothy Robinson early in the third quarter before adding a 1-yard touchdown run. Mario Sanchez hit his third field goal for Prairie View (4-6, 2-6) to pull within 14-9 with 18 seconds left in the third. But a minute later Luke connected with Anthony Mitchell on a 70-yard touchdown pass and the game wasn't close again. Luke was 10-of-21 for 237 yards and two touchdowns. He also ran for 30 yards and a score. Prairie View piled up 279 yards rushing, led by Ben Boyd's 118 on three carries. Arnell Fontenot had 114 on 27 attempts. The Panthers had trouble in the passing game, with Michael Hill connecting on 9 of 23 passes for 91 yards and three interceptions. He connected with Chris Peters on a 6-yard score with four seconds left.
